The GeoTIFF files show land use/land cover for India between
1960 and 2010. Non-null pixels have a value between 1 to 9
representing various land use/land cover classes, as follows:

1 - Cropland
2 - Forest
3 - Grassland
4 - Shrubland
5 - Wasteland
6 - Barren land
7 - Urban
8 - Water bodies
9 - Snow and ice
